@*
    <summary>
    Index page for the Zealand Booking System.

    Responsibility:
    - Acts as the landing page of the application.
    - Adapts the content depending on whether the user is logged in.
    - Guides users towards login, registration, or creating and managing bookings.

    Why this page exists:
    - To give a clear starting point for new and returning users.
    - To explain the system in simple steps and highlight the main actions.
    </summary>
*@
@page
@model Zealand_Booking_System.Pages.IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";

    /// <summary>
    /// Reads the current user's AccountID from the session.
    /// The login state controls which text, buttons and steps are shown on the page.
    /// </summary>
    int? loggedId = HttpContext.Session.GetInt32("AccountID");
}

@*
    <summary>
    Hero section with main message and actions.

    Responsibility:
    - Shows different content for guests and logged-in users.
    - For guests: explains what the system does and who it is for.
    - For logged-in users: pushes them directly towards creating a booking.

    Why this section exists:
    - To quickly communicate the purpose of the system.
    - To highlight the most important next action.
    </summary>
*@
<section class="zb-hero my-4 my-md-5">
    <div class="row align-items-start gy-4">

        @*
            <summary>
            Left side of the hero section.

            Responsibility:
            - Shows welcome text and call-to-action depending on login state.
            - Displays login and registration buttons for guests.
            - Displays booking buttons for logged-in users.

            Why this area exists:
            - To make it obvious what the user should do next
              without reading documentation or menus.
            </summary>
        *@
        <div class="col-lg-6">

            @*
                If the user is not logged in, we show general information and
                a neutral badge. If logged in, we show a strong booking call-to-action.
                This helps guide different user types towards the right action.
            *@
            @if (loggedId == null)
            {
                <span class="zb-badge mb-2">For students & teachers</span>

                <h1 class="zb-hero-title mb-3">
                    Book a study room at Zealand – fast and easy
                </h1>

                <p class="zb-hero-text mb-4 text-light">
                    Find and reserve available rooms for group work, projects, or teaching.
                    The system is designed with clarity and the official Zealand visual identity in mind.
                </p>
            }
            else
            {
                @*
                    Logged-in users already understand the system.
                    Here we focus on the main next step: creating a booking.
                *@
                <span class="zb-badge mb-3"
                      style="background-color:#f7d774;
                             color:black;
                             font-weight:bold;
                             font-size:1.3rem;
                             padding:10px 22px;
                             border-radius:25px;">
                    CREATE A BOOKING NOW!
                </span>
            }

            @*
                Button area.

                Responsibility:
                - For guests: show actions to log in or create an account.
                - For logged-in users: show direct links to booking and booking overview.

                Why this area exists:
                - Users should only see actions they can actually use in their current state.
                - Reduces confusion and clicks by giving the most relevant options.
            *@
            <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                @if (loggedId == null)
                {
                    <a asp-page="/Accounts/Login" class="btn zb-btn-primary px-4 py-2">
                        Log in
                    </a>
                    <a asp-page="/Accounts/Register" class="btn zb-btn-secondary px-4 py-2">
                        Create account
                    </a>
                }
                else
                {
                    <a asp-page="/FindRoom" class="btn zb-btn-primary px-5 py-3" style="font-size:1.2rem;">
                        Create booking
                    </a>

                    <a asp-page="/BookingList" class="btn zb-btn-secondary px-5 py-3" style="font-size:1.2rem;">
                        See your bookings
                    </a>
                }
            </div>

            @*
                Short state message.

                Responsibility:
                - Shows a simple sentence that explains what the user can or cannot do.

                Why this exists:
                - To make the login requirement explicit.
                - To avoid users wondering why they cannot book a room.
            *@
            <p class="small text-light mt-3 mb-0">
                @if (loggedId == null)
                {
                    <span>You must be logged in to book rooms.</span>
                }
                else
                {
                    <span>You are logged in – choose an option above.</span>
                }
            </p>

        </div>

        @*
            <summary>
            Right side of the hero section.

            Responsibility:
            - Displays a step-by-step guide tailored to the login state.
            - For guests: explains the full flow from account creation to booking.
            - For logged-in users: focuses on booking and managing reservations.

            Why this section exists:
            - To visually explain the process in small, clear steps.
            - To reduce uncertainty for first-time users.
            </summary>
        *@
        <div class="col-lg-6">
            <div class="zb-hero-card shadow-sm">
                <h5 class="mb-3 text-light">Next steps</h5>

                @*
                    The steps are different for guests and logged-in users.
                    This avoids showing unnecessary steps and keeps the flow simple.
                *@
                @if (loggedId == null)
                {
                    <ul class="list-unstyled mb-3 small text-light">
                        <li class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="zb-step-number me-2">1</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Create account</strong><br />
                                <span>Register with your Zealand email.</span>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="zb-step-number me-2">2</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Log in</strong><br />
                                <span>Access the booking tools.</span>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="zb-step-number me-2">3</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Go to “Create booking”</strong><br />
                                <span>Select your date and time.</span>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="d-flex">
                            <span class="zb-step-number me-2">4</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Confirm booking</strong><br />
                                <span>Your reservation will appear in “My bookings”.</span>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                }
                else
                {
                    <ul class="list-unstyled mb-3 small text-light">
                        <li class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="zb-step-number me-2">1</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Go to “Create booking”</strong><br />
                                <span>Choose your desired date and room.</span>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="zb-step-number me-2">2</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Make a booking</strong><br />
                                <span>Select date, time slot and room.</span>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="d-flex">
                            <span class="zb-step-number me-2">3</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>See your bookings</strong><br />
                                <span>Manage or cancel your reservations.</span>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                }

                @*
                    Metadata for context.

                    Responsibility:
                    - States that the system is a Datamatiker project from Zealand Roskilde.

                    Why this exists:
                    - Gives reviewers and teachers quick context about origin and purpose.
                *@
                <div class="zb-hero-meta small text-light">
                    <div>Developed as part of a Datamatiker project</div>
                    <div>Zealand · Roskilde</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

@*
    <summary>
    Bottom information section.

    Responsibility:
    - Only shown for users who are not logged in.
    - Explains why the system is useful and highlights key benefits.

    Why this section exists:
    - Acts as a short “sales pitch” to motivate new users to start using the system.
    - Connects the system to real needs: overview, no double bookings, and familiar design.
    </summary>
*@
@if (loggedId == null)
{
    <section class="my-5">
        <h2 class="zb-section-title mb-3">Why use this system?</h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-light">
            The system helps optimize Zealand’s room usage and makes it easy for students
            and teachers to find available rooms for study activities.
        </p>

        <div class="row gy-4 text-light">

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="zb-info-card h-100">
                    <img src="~/images/classroom2.jpg" alt="Overview" />
                    <h5 class="mb-2">Overview of rooms</h5>
                    <p class="small mb-0">
                        View all relevant rooms filtered by campus, size and equipment.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="zb-info-card h-100">
                    <img src="~/images/classroom1.jpg" alt="No double bookings" />
                    <h5 class="mb-2">No double bookings</h5>
                    <p class="small mb-0">
                        The system automatically checks availability and prevents conflicts.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="zb-info-card h-100">
                    <img src="~/images/students.jpg" alt="Designed for students" />
                    <h5 class="mb-2">Designed for students</h5>
                    <p class="small mb-0">
                        Layout and colors inspired by zealand.dk for a familiar experience.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
}
